04551nam a22008655i 9780823263455DE-B159720220302035458.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||220302t20152015nyu    fo  d z      eng d  a97808232634557 a10.1515/97808232634552doi  a(DE-B1597)555030  a(OCoLC)899006902  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  anyucUS-NY 4aPR851b.N36 2015eb 7aLIT0041202bisacsh04a823/.5092231 aNandrea, Lorri G., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut10aMisfit Forms :bPaths Not Taken by the British Novel /cLorri G. Nandrea. 1aNew York, NY : bFordham University Press, c[2015] 4c©2015  a1 online resource (288 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda00tFrontmatter -- tContents -- tAcknowledgments -- tIntroduction: The Novel, Education, and Experience -- t1. Typing Feeling: Sympathy, Sensibility, and Sentimentality -- t2. The Science of the Sensible: From Sterne to Charlotte Brontë -- t3. Sense in the Middle: Teleological vs. Cumulative Plotting -- t4. Verisimilitudes: Curiosity, Wonder, and Negative Capability -- tConclusion: Woolf ’s Fin -- tNotes -- tWorks Cited -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aThe complicated junctions negotiated by the novel during the eighteenth century reveal not only achievements but also exclusions. Misfit Forms offers a speculative reconstruction of roads less traveled. What if typographical emphasis and its associated transmission of sensuality and feeling had not lost out to “transparent” typography and its paradigms of sympathetic identification? What was truncated when cumulative narrative structures were declared primitive in relation to the unified teleological plot? What visions of the novel’s value as an arena for experience were sidelined when novel reading was linked to epistemological gain?Reading novels by Sterne, Charlotte Bronte, Defoe, Gaskell, Hardy, and Woolf in tandem with less-known works, Nandrea illuminates the modes and techniques that did not become mainstream. Following Deleuze, Nandrea traces the “dynamic repetitions” of these junctures in the work of later writers. Far from showing the eclipse of primitive modes, such moments of convergence allow us to imagine other possibilities for the novel’s trajectory.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aEnglish fictiony18th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aEnglish fictiony19th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aSensitivity (Personality trait) in literature. 0aSympathy in literature. 4aLiterary Studies. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / English, Irish, Scottish, Welsh.2bisacsh  aAffect.  aBritish Novel.  aCuriosity.  aDefoe.  aDeleuze.  aDunton.  aEnglish Novel.  aGaskell.  aHistory of the Novel.  aLiterary Theory.  aSensibility.  aSingularity.  aSterne.  aTypography.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertFordham University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311072903040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780823263455zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780823263455423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780823263455/original  a978-3-11-072903-0  Fordham University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK